{{About|the geological feature of Western Australia|other uses|Carnarvon (disambiguation){{!}}Carnarvon}} The '''Carnarvon Basin''' is a geological [[Sedimentary basin|basin]] located in the [[North West Australia|north west]] of [[Western Australia]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ga.gov.au/oceans/rpg_OffNorthWestA.jsp |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2008-06-16 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080805184544/http://www.ga.gov.au/oceans/rpg_OffNorthWestA.jsp |archivedate=2008-08-05 |df= }} for a regional perspective</ref> This is the main geological feature that makes up the [[North West Shelf]]. The onshore part of the Carnarvon Basin covers about 115,000&nbsp;km² and the offshore part covers approximately 535,000&nbsp;km² with water depths up to 3,500 metres. It is separated into two major areas - the Northern Carnarvon Basin, and the Southern Carnarvon Basin.
==Northern Carnarvon Basin== [[File:Regions of western australia nine plus perth.png|thumb|160px|[[Gascoyne (Western Australia)|Gascoyne]] in [[North West Australia]].]] The Northern Carnarvon Basin includes the [[Exmouth Plateau]], Wombat Plateau (on the northern part of the Exmouth Plateau), Investigator Sub-basin, Rankin Platform, Exmouth Sub-basin, Barrow Sub-basin, Dampier Sub-basin, Beagle Sub-basin, Enderby Terrace, Peedamullah Shelf and the Lambert Shelf.<ref name=autogenerated1>[http://www.ga.gov.au/oceans/ofnwa_crnvn_ncb.jsp Geoscience Australia - Northern Carnarvon Basin (NCB)<!-- Bot generated title -->] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090416135418/http://www.ga.gov.au/oceans/ofnwa_crnvn_ncb.jsp |date=April 16, 2009 }}</ref>
The main sub-basins for petroleum exploration in the basin have been Dampier, Exmouth and Barrow.<ref>[http://www.ga.gov.au/oceans/ofnwa_crnvn_PetExp.jsp Geoscience Australia - Petroleum exploration (NCB)<!-- Bot generated title -->] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110321003606/http://www.ga.gov.au/oceans/ofnwa_crnvn_PetExp.jsp |date=March 21, 2011 }}</ref>
==Southern Carnarvon Basin== The Southern basin consists of the Gascoyne, Merlinleigh, Bidgemia and Byro Sub-basins and Bernier Platform and is flanked to the east by the Archaean Pilbara Block.<ref name=autogenerated1 />
==Impact crater== The '''Gnargoo structure''', which has remarkable similarities to [[Woodleigh crater]], is a proposed 75 km impact crater on the Gascoyne Platform, Southern Carnarvon Basin with an estimated age of 100-300 Ma.<ref>R. Iaskty and A. Glikson (2005). "Gnargoo: a possible 75 km-diameter post-Early Permian – pre-Cretaceous buried impact structure, Carnarvon Basin, Western Australia", Australian Journal of Earth Sciences, Vol 52, 2005</ref>
