'''Gill Valentine''' {{post-nominals|country=GBR|FBA}} is a [[geography|geographer]], currently [[Professor]] of Geography and [[Pro-Vice-Chancellor]] of social sciences at the [[University of Sheffield]]. Prior to Sheffield, she was head of Geography at the [[University of Leeds]].<ref>{{cite web|title=University of Sheffield appoints new Pro-Vice-Chancellor for Social Science|url=https://www.sheffield.ac.uk/news/nr/pro-vice-chancellor-social-science-sheffield-1.174461|publisher=Sheffield University|accessdate=3 November 2015}}</ref>
==Research== Valentine is a specialist in [[social geography]], with her key areas of research covering social identities and belonging; childhood, parenting and family life; and urban cultures and consumption.<ref>{{cite web|title=Pro-Vice-Chancellor honoured with top award|url=https://www.sheffield.ac.uk/faculty/social-sciences/news/valentine-murchinson-award-1.461746|publisher=University of Sheffield|accessdate=3 November 2015|date=5 May 2015}}</ref> Her research in particular has focused on geographies of [[childhood]], on alcohol-consumption and youth culture and on women's geographies.<ref name="Profile">{{cite web|title=Professor Gill Valentine|url=https://www.sheffield.ac.uk/geography/staff/valentine_gill|publisher=Sheffield University|accessdate=3 November 2015}}</ref> A co-founder of the journal ''Social & Cultural Geography'' and co-editor of former co-editor of [[Gender, Place and Culture]], she has made significant contributions to [[feminist geography]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Gill Valentine|url=https://uk.sagepub.com/en-gb/eur/author/gill-valentine|publisher=Sage Publications|accessdate=3 November 2015}}</ref> Unusual for a human geographer, her work has received over 21,000 citations as of 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://scholar.google.com.au/citations?user=fp0c7AQAAAAJ&hl=en|title=Gill Valentine - Google Scholar Citations|website=scholar.google.com.au}}</ref>
==Administration== As [[Pro-Vice-Chancellor]] of social sciences she has overall responsibility for this field, and has hired Heads of Departments and reallocated staff over the last few years.
==Awards== *The [[Philip Leverhulme Prize]]<ref name="Profile" /> * The [[Royal Geographical Society]]'s ''Gill Memorial Award'',<ref>{{cite web|title=Full list of medals and awards recipients from 1970 - 2015|url=http://www.rgs.org/NR/rdonlyres/35D66DA7-1C37-4E33-82C2-287D24306318/25709/MedalWinners19702017.pdf|publisher=Royal Geographical Society|accessdate=3 November 2015}}</ref> * [[Murchison Award]] by the Royal Geographical Society for "publications relating to the geography of difference, equality and diversity" (2015)<ref>{{cite web|title=Royal Geographical Society (with IBG) honours top geographers |url=http://www.rgs.org/NR/rdonlyres/A3F2F1A6-26BA-4AA8-A531-EF6DDBDB742E/0/05052015RoyalGeographicalSocietywithIBGhonourstopgeographers_v2.pdf |publisher=Royal Geographical Society |accessdate=3 November 2015 |date=5 May 2015 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151023063739/http://www.rgs.org/NR/rdonlyres/A3F2F1A6-26BA-4AA8-A531-EF6DDBDB742E/0/05052015RoyalGeographicalSocietywithIBGhonourstopgeographers_v2.pdf |archivedate=23 October 2015 |df= }}</ref> *Fellow of the [[Academy of Social Sciences]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Fellows|url=https://www.acss.org.uk/fellows|publisher=Academy of Social Sciences|accessdate=3 November 2015}}</ref> *Fellow of the [[British Academy]] (FBA), 2018<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.britac.ac.uk/news/record-number-academics-elected-british-academy|title=Record number of academics elected to British Academy {{!}} British Academy|website=British Academy|language=en|access-date=2018-07-22}}</ref>
