{{Orphan|date=January 2016}}
[[File:1 Vallee dOosterlog entrance.jpg|thumb|right|Entrance to the Vallee d'Oosterlog garden]]
'''Vallée d'Osterlog''' or '''Osterlog Valley''' is a [[botanical garden]] of Mauritian [[endemism|endemic]] species and a rehabilitated indigenous forest, situated in Le Val, in the south-east of [[Mauritius]].

It was founded on the 11 June 2014.

==Location==
[[File:1 Vallee de Oosterlog.jpg|thumb|left|]]
[[File:Vallee de Oosterlog forest 2.jpg|thumb|right|Endemic forest at the Vallée d'Osterlog]]
The 275 hectare garden & forest is located in the region of Le Val, near [[Le Val Nature Park]] in the south-east of the island. It is in the Creole Mountain range, specifically between Mount Lagrave and Mount Laselle. It also lies almost exactly on the border of two districts - that of Grand Port and Moka. It is reached by road from Le Saint, Hubert Village. The offices of the Vallée d'Osterlog Endemic Garden Foundation are in Wooton, Eau Coulée. 
<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://valleedosterlog.govmu.org/English/Pages/default.aspx|title=Endemic Garden Foundation - Home|last=|first=|date=|website=valleedosterlog.govmu.org|publisher=|access-date=2016-11-03}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://facultyagriculture.blogspot.co.za/2014/06/vallee-dosterlog-endemic-garden.html|title=Vallee d'Osterlog Endemic Garden - Inauguration|website=facultyagriculture.blogspot.co.za|access-date=2016-11-03}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.orange.mu/kinews/dossiers/culture-et-loisirs/374144/inauguration-du-jardin-endemique-de-la-vallee-d-rsquo-osterlog.html|title=Portail Orange Mauritius – ile Maurice|website=www.orange.mu|access-date=2016-11-03}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.lemauricien.com/article/la-vallee-d-osterlog-jardin-entre-deux-montagnes|title=LA VALLÉE D’OSTERLOG : Un jardin entre deux montagnes {{!}} Le Mauricien|website=www.lemauricien.com|access-date=2016-11-03}}</ref>

